{"article_id":"32sfIOF2dmXFLTZp","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The \" compromise \" immigration bill","depth":3},{"id":1,"text":"released Thursday night by Republicans in the House of Representatives","depth":3},{"id":2,"text":"is set to come to the House floor next week , alongside a more conservative alternative .","depth":2},{"id":3,"text":"It ' s a sweeping plan","depth":3},{"id":4,"text":"that covers everything from border security","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"( including a promise of $ 25 billion for Trump ' s border wall ) ;","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"to a way for immigrants","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"who are facing the loss of their protections under the Deferred Action for Childhood Arrivals","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"( DACA )","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"program","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"to apply for legal status and ultimately ( possibly ) green cards and citizenship ;","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"to cuts to legal family-based immigration","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"that are partially offset","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"by expanding permanent employer-based immigration .","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"But House Speaker Paul Ryan and others are emphasizing a different aspect of the bill .","depth":4},{"id":15,"text":"They claim","depth":5},{"id":16,"text":"it would prevent the Trump administration from separating children from their parents at the US-Mexico border","depth":6},{"id":17,"text":"- a practice","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"the administration made widespread in early May","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"and that has resulted in the separation of hundreds of families a week .","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"The Republican bill doesn ' t outlaw family separation .","depth":6},{"id":21,"text":"It doesn ' t stop the Trump administration from choosing to prosecute asylum seekers","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"who enter the US between ports of entry","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"( official border crossings )","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"for illegal entry ,","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"which results in parents being sent into criminal custody","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"without their children .","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"And it doesn ' t even force the government not to separate parents","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"who do present themselves legally for asylum","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"from their children - something","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"that has also been happening ,","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"though isn ' t as widespread .","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"What the House bill does is get rid of the extra legal protections","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"that children and families have in immigration detention :","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"a requirement","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"that children be kept in the \" least restrictive \" conditions possible ,","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"and that they not be detained any longer than necessary .","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"This means","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"that","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"if the family is kept together ,","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"their parents must be released with them .","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"The Trump administration calls those protections \" loopholes , \"","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"and blames them","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"for \" forcing \" the administration to keep asylum-seekers in custody","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"by separating families .","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"If the House bill passed ,","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"the Trump administration probably would stop separating families .","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"Instead , it would be able to keep children and parents in ICE detention","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"until their cases were resolved -","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"that is , they could be in held in detention indefinitely .","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"The House bill allows kids and families to be detained by ICE indefinitely","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"- which is what Trump has wanted all along","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"The Republican summary of the new bill","depth":14},{"id":53,"text":"( as reported by Leigh Ann Caldwell of NBC )","depth":14},{"id":54,"text":"claims","depth":13},{"id":55,"text":"that it ends family separation :","depth":12},{"id":56,"text":"\" Accompanied alien minors","depth":13},{"id":57,"text":"apprehended at the border","depth":13},{"id":58,"text":"must not be separated from their parent or legal guardian while in DHS custody . \"","depth":12},{"id":59,"text":"What exists , however , in a section","depth":14},{"id":60,"text":"called \" Clarification of Standards for Family Detention , \"","depth":14},{"id":61,"text":"is a provision","depth":13},{"id":62,"text":"allowing ICE to detain immigrant children","depth":14},{"id":63,"text":"who come to the US with their parents or guardians","depth":14},{"id":64,"text":"in the same way","depth":14},{"id":65,"text":"it would detain adults :","depth":14},{"id":66,"text":"There exists no presumption","depth":13},{"id":67,"text":"that an alien child","depth":15},{"id":68,"text":"who is not an unaccompanied alien child","depth":15},{"id":69,"text":"should not be detained ,","depth":14},{"id":70,"text":"and all such determinations shall be in the discretion of the Secretary of Homeland Security .","depth":12},{"id":71,"text":"That sentence would overrule a court agreement","depth":12},{"id":72,"text":"that ' s been in place for the past 20 years ,","depth":13},{"id":73,"text":"called the Flores agreement ,","depth":13},{"id":74,"text":"that puts strict limitations on when the government can keep children in immigration detention .","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"The Flores agreement requires","depth":12},{"id":76,"text":"that kids be released","depth":14},{"id":77,"text":"\" without unnecessary delay , \"","depth":14},{"id":78,"text":"and that they are kept in the meantime in the \" least restrictive \" conditions possible .","depth":13},{"id":79,"text":"Courts have interpreted that agreement to mean","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"that ICE can ' t detain families for more than 20 days in most cases .","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"The Flores agreement doesn ' t require the government to separate families .","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"It just requires the government not to indefinitely detain children .","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"But the Trump administration has decided to maximize the detention of asylum seekers ,","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"including parents ,","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"to prevent people from disappearing into the US as unauthorized immigrants","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"after they ' re released .","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"( This is the so-called \" catch and release \" policy","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"Trump has railed against . )","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"Rather than release parents with their children ,","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"therefore , the administration is separating families","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"so the parents can be detained","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"while the children","depth":12},{"id":93,"text":"( sent to the custody of HHS as \" unaccompanied alien children \" )","depth":12},{"id":94,"text":"are ultimately placed with sponsors .","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"The House bill allows the administration to keep families in immigration detention indefinitely .","depth":6},{"id":96,"text":"It doesn ' t even specify","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"that there are any additional conditions","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"on how children can be detained -","depth":11},{"id":99,"text":"there ' s nothing","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"preventing the Trump administration from simply putting children in existing ICE detention centers for adults ,","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"rather than expanding detention centers","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"designed for families .","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"Nothing in the bill requires ICE to keep parents and children together in detention .","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"In fact , the mechanism","depth":12},{"id":105,"text":"that the Trump administration has generally been using","depth":13},{"id":106,"text":"to separate families","depth":13},{"id":107,"text":"- referring parents into the custody of the Department of Justice for prosecution -","depth":11},{"id":108,"text":"isn ' t even addressed in the bill .","depth":10},{"id":109,"text":"The only reason","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"the House bill could possibly end the separation of families","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"would be if the Trump administration decided","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"that","depth":11},{"id":113,"text":"because they now didn ' t have to release children from detention ,","depth":12},{"id":114,"text":"they would stop prosecuting parents ,","depth":12},{"id":115,"text":"and they would make an effort","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"to keep families together in ICE detention .","depth":11},{"id":117,"text":"But even then , that just means that children would be held in facilities","depth":12},{"id":118,"text":"that are essentially jails","depth":12},{"id":119,"text":"with their parents for months , or even years ,","depth":11},{"id":120,"text":"until they ultimately received legal status","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"- or , more likely , until they were finally deported .","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":243,"left":124,"right":242,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":124,"left":123,"right":2,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":123,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":242,"left":134,"right":241,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":134,"left":3,"right":133,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":133,"left":125,"right":132,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":125,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":132,"left":129,"right":131,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":129,"left":128,"right":10,